'''氣態矮星'''是累積了氫、氦、和其他揮發物的厚重氣體殼層，使得其半徑介於1.7至3.9[[地球半徑|地球半徑]]（{{Earth radius|1.7–3.9}}）之間，有著岩石核心的氣態天體。這個名詞通常有三種涵義：以[[金屬量|金屬量]]為基礎分類，也包含岩石類的短週期[[系外行星|系外行星]]；[[類地行星|像地球]]這樣，半徑小於1.7{{Earth radius|1.7}}；和半徑大於{{Earth radius|3.9}}，被稱為[[冰巨星|冰巨星]]和[[氣態巨行星|氣態巨行星]]<ref>[http://arxiv.org/ftp/arxiv/papers/1405/1405.7695.pdf Three regimes of extrasolar planets inferred from host star metallicities] {{Wayback|url=http://arxiv.org/ftp/arxiv/papers/1405/1405.7695.pdf |date=20151107091544 }}, Buchhave et al.</ref>。在[[太陽系|太陽系]]中沒有已知的氣態矮星，但在其它的行星系統中則很常見。

較小的氣態行星和比較接近母恆星的行星，通過流體動力將會比較大的行星和距離較遠的行星更快失去大氣層的質量<ref>{{cite journal | citeseerx = 10.1.1.122.9085 | title = Transonic hydrodynamic escape of hydrogen from extrasolar planetary atmospheres | url = https://archive.org/details/sim_astrophysical-journal_2005-03-10_621_2/page/1049 | author1 = Feng Tian | first2 = Owen B. | last2 = Toon | first3 = Alexander A. | last3 = Pavlov | first4 = H. | last4 = De Sterck | journal = The Astrophysical Journal | volume = 621 | pages = 1049–1060 |date=March 10, 2005 |bibcode = 2005ApJ...621.1049T |doi = 10.1086/427204 }}</ref><ref>[http://arxiv.org/pdf/1001.4851 Mass-radius relationships for exoplanets], Damian C. Swift, Jon Eggert, Damien G. Hicks, Sebastien Hamel, Kyle Caspersen, Eric Schwegler, and Gilbert W. Collins</ref>。

已知氣態行星中體積可能最小的是[[克卜勒138|克卜勒-138d]]，它的質量與[[地球質量|地球]]相似，但是比地球大了60%，因此由它的密度顯示有著厚重的氣體殼層<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.nature.com/news/earth-mass-exoplanet-is-no-earth-twin-1.14477 |title=Earth-mass exoplanet is no Earth twin – Gaseous planet challenges assumption that Earth-mass planets should be rocky |accessdate=2016-12-18 |archive-date=2014-01-07 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140107040338/http://www.nature.com/news/earth-mass-exoplanet-is-no-earth-twin-1.14477 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

一顆低質量的氣態行星，如果有合適的溫度，仍然可以有類似氣態巨行星的半徑<ref>*[http://arxiv.org/abs/1304.5157 Mass-Radius Relationships for Very Low Mass Gaseous Planets] {{Wayback|url=http://arxiv.org/abs/1304.5157 |date=20170914124752 }}, [[Konstantin_Batygin|Konstantin Batygin]], David J. Stevenson, 18 Apr 2013</ref>。

